02:03:24.000 --> 02:03:31.000
Because, I mean, maybe we can at least try to find it out.

02:03:31.000 --> 02:03:35.000
Because, I mean, a couple of different things, I would say.

02:03:35.000 --> 02:03:39.000
One of them would be that the way that you describe it,

02:03:39.000 --> 02:03:49.000
even the endogenous preferences that actually take into account that preferences change over time,

02:03:49.000 --> 02:03:55.000
even those when you describe them, you do acknowledge that people change.

02:03:55.000 --> 02:04:00.000
You do acknowledge that they change through their actions in some way.

02:04:00.000 --> 02:04:10.000
But what you do leave out is this huge area of what might call collective preference formation.

02:04:10.000 --> 02:04:20.000
So it is not only me that is involved in forming my own preferences, neither in the here and now or over time.

02:04:20.000 --> 02:04:30.000
So, and this is if you take this kind of thinking in terms of preferences and then look at the way paracorn is set up,

02:04:30.000 --> 02:04:35.000
then I do see some analogy because you do have these worker councils

02:04:35.000 --> 02:04:41.000
and they interact with each other on a higher level only through parametric mediation.

02:04:41.000 --> 02:04:46.000
And from my perspective, one would say, all right,

02:04:46.000 --> 02:04:55.000
it's nice and fine that worker councils within their internal structures are structured democratically and self-organized and stuff like that.

02:04:55.000 --> 02:05:03.000
But the preference formation on a higher scale is always and needs to be also a political process,

02:05:03.000 --> 02:05:14.000
not only a communication, but a very much political process because this aspect of collective preference formation needs to be that, exactly that, collective.

02:05:14.000 --> 02:05:21.000
But through modeling these actions in paracorn in the way that you do,

02:05:21.000 --> 02:05:32.000
you will necessarily lead yourself into a position where you can only argue for workers councils acting with each other on a parametric level

02:05:32.000 --> 02:05:38.000
because you do not want to interfere with the, so to speak, personal integrity of the workers councils.

02:05:38.000 --> 02:05:40.000
So there you have this analogy.

02:05:40.000 --> 02:05:44.000
And this is interesting to me how one relates to the other

02:05:44.000 --> 02:05:50.000
and how I would argue both on the individual level as well as on the societal level

02:05:50.000 --> 02:05:56.000
for an aspect which I would then call maybe collective preference formation,

02:05:56.000 --> 02:06:04.000
which would always entail certain political aspect and political mechanisms

02:06:04.000 --> 02:06:13.000
that are not addressed sufficiently through, for example, mere parametric mediation, I would say.

02:06:13.000 --> 02:06:15.000
I hope I'm a bit clear.

02:06:15.000 --> 02:06:18.000
I think I hear you.

02:06:18.000 --> 02:06:25.000
I mean, one thing I would say is that there's actually a difference of opinion between Michael Albert and me on this subject.

02:06:25.000 --> 02:06:36.000
